{ This move has been seen from time to time, playing in the style of the Chebanenko Slav. Black is unwilling to commit his knight to d7 just yet and may look to play c6-c5 and develop the knight to c6 in various cases. Anand used it to great effect, easily neutralizing Boris Gelfand for much of their 2012 World Championship match, but the move has not stood the test of time too well. }
